  The Review

    What are the contributions of the paper?

    a tool for image assessment reusing existing workflow methods.

    What are its strengths and weaknesses?

    Strengths:
    + The methodology of capturing the needs and designing the tool. This is how the
    design work should be carried out.
    + capturing the needs from a relatively large population.
    + showing provenance through interaction seems to be good.

    Weaknesses:
    - it is unclear to me how user's intent is captured here, since those interaction
    are not mutual exclusive or independent. Take Figure 4 as an example, it s unclear
    if the user's rotation is for explore or for select. Thus the node aggregation
    seems to be somewhat arbitrary.

    Is this work relevant for the EuroVis conference?

    Yes.

    Is relevant previous work adequately referenced? If not, what citations should be
    added?

    yes.

    Is the paper technically sound?

    Yes, somewhat (see the weakness above.)

    Could it be reproduced by a skilled graduate student?

    Yes.

    Is the exposition clear? How could the structure or style of the presentation be
    improved?

    Yes. the paper is easy to understand and well written. Please use the third-person
    to refer to yourself, when citing your own work. Otherwise, the paper is not
    anonymous, unfair to other paper authors.

    Should anything be deleted or condensed from the writeup?
    Yes.
    Are the figures as informative as possible?
    Yes.
    Is the (optional) supplementary material helpful (if provided)?
    N/P

