committee member review
score 3/5

  Paper Type

    Application / Design Study

  Rating

    Borderline: the strengths and weaknesses balance for this paper.

  Expertise

    Expert

  The Review

    The paper "Improving Provenance Data Interaction for Visual Storytelling in
    Medical Imaging Data Exploration" aims to give guidelines on how to improve the
    interaction with prominance data displayed in a graph in order to facilitate
    auhoring and the creation of visual data stories.

    The paper is well written und well structured. It gives an good overview over the
    requirements and carefully summarizes the needs of the underlying user group.

    My big issue with this paper is that the requirements and guidelines made by the
    authors are very vague. Although this is a short paper I would at least expect one
    evaluation setting with a user group from the medical domain or at least user
    statements if the presented approach fits their needs.

    As the paper states in the title, the system is especially designed for medical
    purposes. Besides some minor statements I don't see how this system differs from
    setting in other domains. I am also missing an concrete example on how the system
    is used in a specific task (surgery or treatment planning would be nice here).

    Overall, I will rate this contribution as a borderline as I am not sure if the
    provided content is enough for a paper and the reasing for the presented
    requirements and settings is missing.

